<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Lobbies GATT on Trade-Environment Link </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2502054594 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2502054594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thailand is calling on the General Agreement on 
Tariffs and Trade to stop linking trade issues to environmental 
concerns. The deputy minister for science, technology, and 
environment, Pricha Musikun, made the request at an informal 
meeting on trade and the environment in Geneva, Switzerland, 
attended by more than 20 nations. 
  The gathering was organized as a brainstorming session ahead 
of the signing of the new Uruguay GATT agreement in April. 
Thailand and Malaysia attended the meeting as representatives 
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations, or ASEAN. Mr. 
Pricha said developed nations should not make environmental 
demands as part of any trade negotiations with developing 
countries. He said it is important that all nations be allowed 
to develop at their own pace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

