<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mongolian President on Official Visit 25-28 Feb </TI></H3>
<H4>   Air Service Agreement Signed </H4>
<F P=102> BK2502130594 Bangkok Voice of Free Asia in Thai 1030 GMT 25 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2502130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Voice of Free Asia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An air service agreement was signed between the Thai 
and Mongolian Governments at Government House toady. The Thai 
Government was represented by Foreign Minister Squadron Leader 
Prasong Sunsiri, while the Mongolian trade and industry minister 
signed on behalf of his government. Prime Minister Chuan 
Likphai and Mongolian President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat witnessed 
the signing. 
  A Mongolian delegation visited Thailand from 15-16 September 
to negotiate an air service agreement, and a draft agreement was 
initialed on 16 September. The Mongolian president's 25-28 
February visit to Thailand presented a good opportunity to sign 
the initialed air service agreement. 
  Flights by the two countries' airlines will commence when 
each is ready. The agreement will facilitate visits by people 
from the two countries and promote tourism, trade, and 
investment as well as cultural and art exchanges between the two 
nations. 
  Thailand currently has air service agreements with 72 
countries; 69 airlines from 55 countries fly to Thailand on 
regular basis, averaging 532.5 flights per week. 

</TEXT>

