<H3> <TI>   Conference Opens on 30th Anniversary of Theses </TI></H3>
<H4>   `World Public' Lends Praise </H4>
<F P=102> SK2402152294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1507 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2402152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["`Theses on Socialist Rural Question in Our Country Is </F>
Great Programme for Rural Construction'" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- The world public is 
unanimously praising the "Theses on the Socialist Rural Question 
in Our Country" published by the great leader President Kim 
Il-song as a great programme for the socialist rural 
construction which gives a perfect scientific exposition of all 
the theoretical and practical questions arising in the solution 
of the rural question for the first time in human history. 
  Aubrey G. Thomas, chairman of the group for the study of the 
chuche idea of Comrade Kim Il-song in Goedverwagting, Guyana, 
said that the ideas expounded by respected President Kim Il-song 
in the rural theses were the unique idea elucidating a clear 
vista of solving the rural question and great idea indicating 
the right way of completely liberating the farmers freed from 
exploitation and oppression even from the fetters of old ideas 
and nature. 
  The Egyptian paper AKHER SA'A wrote that President Kim 
Il-song created the chuche method of farming after his earnest 
study while personally raising crops in the garden for the 
settlement of the rural question and applied it to farming. 
  The Central African news agency said that the development of 
agriculture in Korea was made entirely by the wise guidance of 
the respected leader President Kim Il-song, adding that Korea 
has firmly laid the powerful material and technical foundations 
which make it possible to endlessly increase agricultural 
production, unaffected in any unfavourable condition. 
  The Syrian paper NIDAL PALYAHIN said that the farmers of 
Korea are now leading a rich and cultural life; like in towns. 
  The Zambian paper ZAMBIA DAILY MAIL in an article stressed 
that the countryside of Korea built by the great President Kim 
Il-song reminds us of paradise or utopia pictured by ancient 
people to themselves. 

</TEXT>

