<H3> <TI>   South Reportedly Commits `Military Provocation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2502104194 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0900 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2502104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0900 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 25 February, the South Korean puppets committed a 
grave military provocation by firing a large-caliber artillery 
gun against the areas on our side. 
  Around 1053 [0153 GMT] today, the armed rascals of the South 
Korean puppet army, who were entrenched in Taeyongpyong Island, 
fired a 155 mm gun against Changje Island at our side on the sea 
off (Pokpo) in Kangnyong County, South Hwanghae Province. 
Because of this, fishermen of our side, who were catching fish 
in the area, were gravely threatened. 
  Such action by the South Korean puppets has not escalated 
into an armed conflict between the two sides. This is totally 
due to our People's Army soldiers' high sense of patience and 
self-control. 
  The dangerous military provocation by the South Korean 
puppets -- which was committed in broad daylight -- is a 
deliberate provocation to lead the Korean peninsula to 
confrontation and war. 
  We regard such provocation by the South Korean puppets as 
even more grave because they committed it at the same time of 
their persistent strategy and war maneuvers in order to crush 
[apsal] our Republic, the socialist fortress, in collusion with 
outside forces under the pretext of our non-existent nuclear 
issue. 
  With a high sense of the revolutionary alertness, our people 
and the People's Army soldiers are keenly watching out the new 
war provocations by the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean 
puppets. 
  Because of the U.S. imperialists' and the South Korean 
puppets' continuous new war provocations, a grave touch-and-go 
situation has been created on the Korean peninsula. Therefore, 
they must clearly see it and must not act recklessly. 
  Despite our repeated warnings, if the South Korean puppets 
continue to embark upon the road of confrontation and war, 
warmongers cannot avoid the stern punishment. 

</TEXT>

