<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports `Grave Provocation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2502115794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1117 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2502115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["South Korean Puppets Commit Grave Military Provocation" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
puppets committed a grave provocation today by firing a 
large-calibre gun into the area of the North side. 
  At around 10:53 the armed bandits of the South Korean Puppet 
Army entrenched on the Taeyonpyong Islet fired their 155 mm gun 
toward the Changjae Islet of the North side on the West Sea of 
Korea off Pupo, Kangnyong County, South Hwanghae Province. 
  In this the safety of the fishermen of the North side 
engaged 
in fishing around the islet was seriously threatened. 
  It was entirely thanks to the great patience and 
self-control 
of soldiers of the Korean People's Army that the artillery fire 
of the South Korean puppets did not expand into an armed 
conflict between the two sides. 
  This dangerous military provocation committed by the South 
Korean puppets in broad daylight was a premeditated act intended 
to drive the situation on the Korean peninsula to confrontation 
and war. 
  We cannot but take a serious view of the South Korean 
puppets' provocation because it was timed to coincide with 
their tenacious plots and war moves to stifle the DPRK, the 
bulwark of socialism, over its fictitious "nuclear issue", hand 
in glove with outside forces. 
  The Korean people and People's Army soldiers are sharply 
watching with heightened revolutionary vigilance the new war 
provocation moves of the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean 
puppets. 
  The U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets must 
refrain from rash acts, looking straight at the touch-and-go 
situation on the Korean peninsula caused by their continuous 
provocations for a new war. 
  If the South Korean puppets keep to the line of 
confrontation 
and war, defying our repeated warnings, those warmaniacs will be 
sternly punished. 

</TEXT>

