<F P=106> [KYODO/YONHAP report from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] Chinese President Jiang Zemin invited North Korean 
President Kim Il-song to visit China at the latter's convenience 
some time this year. The Chinese Government news agency XINHUA 
reported in a news dispatch from Pyongyang. XINHUA said that Li 
Shuzheng, head of the CPC International Liaison Department, 
conveyed President Jiang Zemin's desire for the invitation when 
she, on a visit to Pyongyang, visited President Kim yesterday. 
XINHUA said that President Kim expressed gratitude for this and 
expressed his desire to visit China when the opportunity arises. 

