<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Says Kim Chong-il To Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2502105994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1011 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2502105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, Feb. 25 (YONHAP) -- China has invited 
North Korean President Kim Il-song to visit Beijing some time 
this year after March, a month when top South Korean and 
Japanese leaders would visit China, the SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST 
reported on Friday. The daily, quoting Chinese diplomatic 
sources, said Kim Chong-il, the heir to and son of Kim Il-song, 
would also visit China before summer this year. The sources 
observed it is almost certain that Kim Il-song would accept the 
Chinese invitation. 
  The paper quoted the sources as saying that China is 
inviting 
the top leaders of South and North Korea and Japan in a move to 
demonstrate its influence in Northeast Asia. It seems Kim 
Il-song would ask for China's economic aid and cooperation and 
also its support for Kim Chong-il as the next ruler of North 
Korea, the POST said. Kim Il-song is also interested in meeting 
China's paramount leader Deng Xiaoping to affirm the "lips and 
teeth relations" between China and North Korea, said the paper 
adding that Deng would agree to meet Kim on a private basis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

