<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Provide PLO $12 Million in Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2502104794 Seoul YONHAP in English 1007 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2502104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 25 (YONHAP) -- South Korea has decided 
to provide the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) with 12 
million dollars in economic cooperation funds in the next five 
years, the Foreign Ministry reported on Friday. The amount will 
comprise 2 million dollars in grant and 10 million dollars in 
economic development cooperation fund (EDCF). 
  The ministry said that this year, 260,000 dollars will be 
disbursed for use in financing the training of 10 Palestine 
technical students in Korea, dispatch of two Korean specialists 
to Palestine and the supply of various equipment and materials, 
the ministry report said. A ministry official said the 
cooperation fund is part of international efforts to support the 
autonomy of Palestine. 
  "PLO's aid recipient office has not been singled out yet, 
but 
we are studying a plan to furnish the cooperation fund through 
the Palestine economic development and reconstruction committee 
headed by PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat," he said. 

</TEXT>

