<H3> <TI>   Honda on More Exports From U.S. `Transplant' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2402031094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0229 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2402031094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 24 KYODO -- Honda Motor Co. will try to 
boost exports from its U.S. Ohio transplant this year by 80 
percent from last year to 75,000 vehicles, positioning it as the 
largest auto exporter in the United States, a company official 
said Thursday [24 February]. 
  "We will be increasing exports to Japan of our Accord and 
Civic models from Honda of America Manufacturing Inc. Our 
decision was backed by strong demand in Japan, as well as by the 
appreciation of the yen against the dollar," the official said. 
  The decision was also made in line with the commencement of 
sales in Japan on March 1 of Ohio-made Accord wagons and Accord 
coupes, he said. 
  Honda of America's top export regions will be Japan, 
followed 
by Taiwan, Europe, Israel and Latin America. A few more 
countries in Latin America could be added to the U.S. unit's 
current list of 28 export countries, bringing the total as high 
as 32, the official said. 

</TEXT>

