Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 25 KYODO -- Japan will brief 12 former 
Soviet republics on its measures on arms control, disarmament 
and nonproliferation when it holds a seminar on export control 
March 7- 11, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [25 February]. 
  The seminar will be the first including all 12 former Soviet 
republics to discuss controls on the export of technology with 
military applications and will be sponsored by the Foreign 
Ministry in cooperation with the Ministries of Finance, and 
International Trade and Industry. 
  The seminar is designed to assist the former republics in 
establishing an effective export control system in order to 
strengthen the nonproliferation of arms, the ministry said. 

