<F P=102>  OW2402112094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1055 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2402112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 24 KYODO -- Twenty legislators mainly 
from the major opposition Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) in the 
Diet attended a meeting Thursday [24 February] to prepare for 
establishing a policy study group, the attendants said. Seiichi 
Ota and Shokei Arai, both LDP members of the House of 
Representatives, and two independents are among them. 
  Organizers of the group hope to officially launch their new 
team called "Liberals" in early March. They also hope to have 
the participation of more Diet members, local assembly members, 
