<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troops Arrive in Bosnia After Delay in Croatia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2502085794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2502085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A total of 500 Malaysian troops serving with the 
United Nations, UN, have been deployed in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
after being delayed in Croatia. Defense Minister Datuk Sri 
Najib Tun Razak said 65 men in two platoons were deployed around 
the Mount Igman area overlooking the besieged capital of 
Sarajevo while the rest were in Konjic and Visoko. 
  He said the delay was due to the land route through 
neighboring Croatia to Bosnia proper being blocked by obstacles 
and the winter weather conditions. He told this to reporters 
after receiving 7,200 packets of goodies for the end of Ramadan 
celebration. The goodies will be flow by Hercules transport 
aircraft to the Malaysian troops in Bosnia. 
  A total of 2,555 Malaysian military personnel are serving 
with the UN peacekeeping operation worldwide, including Somalia 
and their staff officers at the world body headquarters in New 
York. 

</TEXT>

