<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Excludes British From New Contracts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2502102094 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2502102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Datuk Sri Anwar Ibrahim has 
announced that the cabinet has decided not to entertain 
participation by British companies in new contracts, especially 
those funded by the government. He said this in Kuala Lumpur 
today following British press reports of the alleged tactics 
used by the British Government and British companies in winning 
Malaysian contracts. The alleged arms-for-aid deal has prompted 
the House of Commons Select Committee on Foreign Affairs to 
launch an investigation into the Pergau Dam affair. 

</TEXT>

