<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Keating Expresses Sympathy for Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2802060094 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0100 GMT 
28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2802060094 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Paul Keating has expressed his 
sympathy for victims of the massacre of Palestinians in the West 
Bank town of Hebron. More than 50 people were killed in the 
attack by a Jewish gunman. In his response, Mr. Keating 
emphasized the need for peace in the region. He said he was 
appalled by what had happened and could only hope that it did 
not derail the reconciliation in the Middle East. Earlier, the 
foreign minister, Gareth Evans, urged both Israel and the 
Palestine Liberation Organization to intensify their efforts for 
peace. 

</TEXT>

