<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry has, in the meantime, reported 
that a group of men, supporters of Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, last 
night gravely violated public order in Bled. The Foreign 
Ministry informed Yuri Stepanovich Girenko, charge d'affaires of 
the Russian Embassy in Ljubljana, about the event that had 
disturbed some of the Slovene public and advised that Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy and his men leave the territory of the Republic of 
Slovenia as soon as possible. 

