<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Christmas' Cease-Fire Extended to 28 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101104194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0951 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 31 Jan (TANJUG) -- Representatives of the 
republic of Srpska army [VRS] and the Croatian Army yesterday 
signed another agreement -- with the mediation of the UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] -- on the extension of the so-called 
Christmas cease-fire. The extended cease-fire agreement comes 
into effect at 0000 this evening. The warring sides signed 
their first cease-fire agreement -- the Christmas cease-fire -- 
on 17 December last year and on 13 January extended it until 
midnight on 31 January. The extended truce will be in effect 
until 28 February this year. The VRS General Staff said that 
both sides were prepared to resume negotiations on a general 
cease-fire. 

</TEXT>

