<H3> <TI>   Bulgarian Defense Delegation Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Partnership,' Balkans Discussed </H4>
<F P=102> AU2801171194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2801171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A military delegation led by Bulgarian Defense 
Minister Valentin Aleksandrov arrived in Bucharest today. The 
delegation had talks with a military delegation led by 
Lieutenant General Niculae Spiroiu, Romanian minister of 
national defense. The sides discussed issues pertaining to 
NATO's initiative on the Partnership for Peace, the situation in 
the former Yugoslav territory and its impact on the Balkans, and 
measures taken thus far to restructure and modernize the 
military bodies of the two neighboring countries. 
  The sides also pointed out their joint desire to develop the 
traditional relations of friendship and cooperation between the 
two armies, concludes a fax received from the Army's Press 
Bureau. 

