<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Supports Preservation of Visegrad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101144794 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1300 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Slovak President Michal Kovac spoke today in favor 
of preserving the Visegrad Group's role as a practical 
consultative forum, without its being institutionalized. He 
said that mutual cooperation of Central European countries would 
help to speed up the inevitable economic changes and their 
incorporation into the well-tried European structures. 
  Replying to a question about whether in his opinion the 
Visegrad Group could exist without the Czech Republic, President 
Kovac said that, in the talks he had in Prague, there was no 
indication that the Czech Republic was not interested in mutual 
cooperation. President Kovac therefore does not think it 
appropriate to consider other alternatives to the Visegrad Group. 

</TEXT>

