<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clearing Account for Slovak Trade Exceeds Limit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3101165294 Prague DENNI TELEGRAF in Czech 29 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU3101165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague DENNI TELEGRAF </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The Balance of the Clearing Account </F>
Just Like at the End of Last Year"] 
  [Text] Prague--The overall balance of the clearing account 
for trade with Slovakia has reached 5.7 billion korunas or 
approximately 170 million ECU's, after Thursday [27 January], 
which is 40 million ECU's over the margin limit. 
  The old lot surplus amounts to 800 million korunas, and the 
new lot 4.9 billion in favor of the Czech Republic. Last year, 
at the end of December, when the margin limit was surpassed for 
the first time, the amounts reached 1.611 billion and 4.106 
billion, respectively. The National Bank of the Slovak Republic 
covered the amount over the allowed margin before the deadline 
on 10 January. 

</TEXT>

