<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak To Sign Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102121294 Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish 1100 GMT 1 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TV Polonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Announcer] The Council of Ministers will 
authorize Prime ministerr Waldemar Pawlak to sign documents in 
Brussels tomorrow on Poland's entry to the Partnership for Peace 
program. 
  Dorota Warakomska is currently outside the Council of 
Ministers' meeting room as ministers are going into the cabinet 
meeting: 
  [Warakomskais] Will the prime minister sign the Partnership 
for Peace tomorrow in Brussels? 
  [Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski] I think so. The 
Council 
of Ministers will ask him to do so. In any case, that is what I 
will be proposing. There is no reason why he will not sign. 
  [Announcer] [passage omitted] Before the cabinet meeting, 
Deputy Prime Minister Marek Borowski did not reply to a question 
asking if the prime minister had explained to him the reasons 
for the dismissal of Deputy Finance Minister Stefan Kawalec. 
Asked the same question, Prime Minister Pawlak answered simply: 
I've explained [wyjasnilem]. 

</TEXT>

