<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "They Have Returned I. Lexa's Documents"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Ivan Lexa, head of the Government 
Office, has informed TA SR that officers from the Slovak 
Republic Police Force returned his travel documents to him 
yesterday evening and told him that, after "reevaluating the 
situation, there are no longer any reasons for holding on to 
them." In view of the fact that my documents were seized--on 
written authorization--a month ago on account of "the nature of 
my criminal activity" and that the legal proceedings being taken 
against me in accordance with Paragraph 103 of the Criminal Law 
are continuing, I do not understand the current course of 
action, said Lexa. At the same time, he described this 
situation as a manifestation of the rash behavior and excessive 
initiative coupled with a lack of professionalism displayed by 
the law enforcement agencies a month ago. 

</TEXT>

