<F P=102>  AU0102135594 Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak 31 Jan 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU0102135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Prices Went up in December Also"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--According to an analysis by the Slovak 
Statistical Office, consumer prices rose by 0.6 percent in 
December. Over the 12 months of 1993, however, in comparison 
with December of 1992, the prices grew by 16.7 percent, and in 
comparison with all of 1992 by 23.2 percent. Inflation 
increased in December last year by 0.6 percent in comparison 
with November and by 23.2 percent in comparison with the average 
of 1992. The increase in the price of eggs and egg products 
(4.1 percent) is most responsible for the overall increase in 
the price of food products (0.3 percent). In the nonfood group, 
prices rose by 0.2 percent in most of the categories surveyed, 
and by 0.5 percent in transportation and sporting accessories. 

</TEXT>

