<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vukovar Official Protests Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101203594 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Correspondent] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's visit to 
Vukovar and the occupied areas of the Vukovar and Srijem county, 
i.e. Sector East where a Russian UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
battalion is deployed, was a point on the agenda of a Vukovar 
and Srijem Assembly session today, from which a protest note was 
sent to the Russian embassy saying among other things: 
  [Begin recording] [Matej Jankovic, prefect of the Vukovar 
and 
Srijem County] Therefore, I consider it your duty to dissociate 
yourself from the visit and activities of your parliamentarians, 
while UNPROFOR in which your soldiers are also deployed, has a 
duty to prevent Zhirinovskiy from entering an area within the 
internationally recognized borders of the Republic of Croatia 
without permission by relevant bodies of our state. [end 
recording] 
  [Correspondent] It should be noted that the Croatian side 
has 
never opposed any visits either to Sector East or the UNPROFOR 
forces that was regularly announced or organized in cooperation 
with relevant Croatian bodies. 

