<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bulgarian Defense Delegation Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Cooperation Accord Signed </H4>
<F P=102> AU2901193494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2901193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today Romanian President Ion Iliescu received a 
military delegation of the Republic of Bulgaria led by Bulgarian 
Minister of Defense Valentin Aleksandrov. After the meeting, 
the Bulgarian guest expressed his satisfaction with the talks 
held with the head of the Romanian state. 
  At the end of the visit of the Bulgarian military 
delegation, 
Mr. Valentin Aleksandrov held a news conference that was 
attended also by Lieutenant General Niculae Spiroiu, Romania's 
minister of defense, and by members of the leadership of the 
Romanian National Defense Ministry. The journalists were 
presented the content of the accord of cooperation between the 
two armies signed this morning by the defense ministers of 
Romania and of Bulgaria. 
  The document provides for cooperation in the area of 
training 
personnel, instructing troops, control in the area of 
disarmament, in the technological, economic, and medical areas 
and in social and sports activities. 
  Minister Valentin Aleksandrov discussed the importance of 
this document saying that it is a new step toward strengthening 
relations between the two armies and it will make a contribution 
to increasing confidence between Romania and Bulgaria. 
  Other issues approached during this news conference were 
connected with ensurance of security in the Balkan region and in 
the whole of Europe, as well as ways to approach the issue of 
war in the former Yugoslavia. The sides noted that the two 
states have common viewpoints on ways to find solutions to this 
conflict. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

