<F P=101> Inter-European Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   WEU Embargo Patrol Detains Bulgarian Vessel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102122194 Sofia BTA in English 1025 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0102122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the BTA press review] </F>
  [Text] Sofia, February 1 (BTA) -- DEMOKRATSIYA and 
OTECHESTVEN VESTNIK carry front-page reports on the detention of 
a Bulgarian ship carrying oil by an embargo patrol of the 
Western European Union [WEU] near Calafat, Romania. The tugboat 
Khan Krum and three barges carried 5,000 tonnes of diesel fuel, 
the dailies say. The convoy tried to pass by the port of Ruse 
with its lights off, obviously attempting to reach the Serbian 
port upstream, DEMOKRATSIYA, the daily of the Union of the 
Democratic Forces (SDS), reports. According to the daily, the 
boat was hired by Multigroup. This is not the first time that 
this financial grouping is named in connection with a 
sanctions-busting attempt, the two dailies write. 

</TEXT>

