<H3> <TI>   Yordanov Returns From `Successful' Kuwait Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701152794 Sofia BTA in English 1422 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, January 27 (BTA) -- National Assembly 
Chairman Aleksandur Yordanov assessed as extremely successful 
the visit to Kuwait by a Bulgarian parliamentary delegation 
headed by him. 
  On his return today, Mr. Yordanov said the delegation had 
been received by top state officials, Kuwait's Amir Shaykh Jabir 
al-Ahmad al-Jabir al-Sabah, Crown Prince and Prime Minister 
Shaykh Sa'ad al-'Abdallah al-Salim al-Sabah, and the speaker of 
the National Assembly. He said the Bulgarian MP's had been 
warmly greeted at the Kuwaiti Parliament. 
  They all stressed the significant role played by Bulgaria 
and 
the democratic forces in particular in support of Kuwait's cause 
during the Iraqi aggression, Mr. Yordanov said. 
  Asked by BTA whether Kuwaiti businessmen were ready to 
invest 
in Bulgaria, Mr. Yordanov stressed they were showing interest 
but Bulgaria had to remove certain obstacles. "We are the ones 
who lack a successful policy of attracting foreign investment," 
he said. 
  Mr. Yordanov pointed out the sides had reached full 
understanding over the entry into Kuwait of more Bulgarian 
engineering and construction firms, as well as of food makers. 

</TEXT>

