<H3> <TI>   Ministry Views Ukrainian Nuclear Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2801195394 Prague CTK in English 1755 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2801195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Jan 28 (CTK) -- The Czech Foreign Ministry 
considers the fulfilling of the January 14 trilateral 
declaration by the presidents of the United States, Russia and 
Ukraine on removing nuclear weapons from Ukraine a significant 
step towards the strengthening of European stability and 
non-proliferation of nuclear weapons throughout the world. 
  In a statement given to CTK today, the Ministry praises the 
attitude by Ukrainian president Leonid Kravchuk and expresses 
its support of Kravchuk's efforts at attaining the passage of 
the document by the Ukrainian Parliament. 
  Since its birth on January 1, 1993, the Czech Republic has 
been striving to establish advantageous and long-term relations 
with Ukraine. By this it wants to contribute to strengthening 
Ukrainian statehood, which it views as an important condition of 
European security, Ministry Spokesman Vit Kurfurst told CTK. 

