<H3> <TI>   Romanian Party Sends Message to MSZP </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102090794 Budapest MTI in English 2033 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0102090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 31 January (MTI) -- The ruling Party of 
Social Democracy in Romania (PDSR) holds the view that 
sober-minded forces in Romania and Hungary may succeed in 
normalizing bilateral relations in the soonest possible time, 
including the conclusion of a basic treaty. 
  This is contained in the message PDSR Chairman Oliviu 
Gherman 
has sent to the Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP). The message 
was handed over to MSZP Chairman Gyula Horn by a delegation led 
by Romanian Ambassador Ion Donca today [31 January]. Horn told 
MTI that the message was a reaction to former MSZP statements on 
Hungary's relations with its neighbours. 
  Signed by Gherman, the message stresses that the PDSR met 
with a great deal of satisfaction the Hungarian socialists' 
position calling for a historical reconciliation between Hungary 
and its neighbours, including Romania. 
  In Gherman's view, this reconciliation should be confirmed 
by 
a basic treaty, which would recognize the current borders and, 
on the basis of international norms, contain mutual commitments 
to guaranteeing minority rights. 
  The settlement and development of relations would promote 
the 
two countries' integration into the Euro-Atlantic system and 
facilitate their democratic transformation, runs the message. 
  In reply to it, Horn confirmed that the MSZP was pressing 
for 
Budapest and Bucharest to conclude a basic treaty, declaring 
both the inviolability of borders and the full enforcement of 
ethnic minority rights. 
  In the MSZP's view, Hungary and Romania are interdependent 
as 
far as their relationship with European integration 
organizations is concerned. Thus they should not act against 
one another, on the contrary, they should make every possible 
joint effort to enforce their interests in this field. 

</TEXT>

