<H3> <TI>   Transport Union Stages Protest Rally </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3101183794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1720 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3101183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 31/1/1994 -- The national 
federation of the transport unions, Elcatel, called Monday, 31 
January, a protest rally in front of the transport ministry 
building to express their dissatisfaction with the attitude 
taken by the Romanian National Railway Corporation (SNCFR) and 
the relevant ministry to the "serious problems" railway 
employees have to endure and with the hazards arising from such 
an attitude. 
  Among the reasons of discontent are the delay in the debate 
and passing of the railway transportation bill, the persisting 
economic blockage, and the compensation by the government of 
railway tariffs. 
  Should their claims be disregarded, Elcatel promised 
concerted strikes on 15 February, to be then extended to a 
general strike on 17 February. 

</TEXT>

