<H3> <TI>   Parliament Ratifies Ukrainian Border Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701214594 Prague CTK in English 2119 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Jan 27 (CTK) -- The Slovak Parliament 
today ratified the treaty between Slovakia and Ukraine on a 
common border and cooperation in questions. The treaty was 
signed on October 14, 1993. The treaty confirms the current 
border, and provides for the marking of the border on the 
terrain and for maintenance of the markers. It also provides 
for the creation of a joint commission to monitor compliance 
with the treaty. It will remain in force for ten years and 
supersedes a similar treaty between Czechoslovakia and the 
Soviet Union signed in 1973, when Ukraine was still a Soviet 
Republic. 

</TEXT>

