<H3> <TI>   Iranian Foreign Minister Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Velayati Meets With Zhelev </H4>
<F P=102> AU0202072694 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 1 February Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati, who is in Bulgaria on an official two-day visit, met 
with National Assembly Chairman Aleksandur Yordanov, President 
Zhelev, and Prime Minister Berov. 
  The possibilities of activating trade and economic 
cooperation between Bulgaria and Iran was at the center of all 
the talks. Special attention was devoted to the project of 
developing new transportation links between the Caucasus and the 
Black Sea, banking and legal relations, and the manner of making 
trade payments. 
  The situation in the Balkans also was discussed. The two 
sides expressed their satisfaction with the failure of the 
attempt against Iranian President Rafsanjani. 
  Dr. Zhelev assured the Iranian foreign minister that the 
situation of the Muslims in Bulgaria had fundamentally changed 
in the last years and that their rights had been restored. 

</TEXT>

