<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   EBRD Turns Down Request for Assistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102181294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1620 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 1 Feb (TANJUG) -- Jacques de Larosiere, 
president of the European Bank for Reconstruction and 
Development, today informed Radoje Kontic, prime minister of the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia [FRY], that the bank cannot send 
a mission for talks with Yugoslav experts on the reconstruction 
of the country's monetary system because the FRY is not 
currently a member of this international institution. Kontic 
had sent a letter to the European Bank at the beginning of 
January, requesting that a mission of this bank pay a visit to 
Yugoslavia in order to discuss the reconstruction of the 
monetary system with Yugoslav experts. 
  Larosiere believes that the FRY government should remain in 
contact with the bank's board of governors concerning its 
readmission, but at the same time expressed doubt that the 
bank's members would wish to tackle this issue before the 
sanctions against Yugoslavia are lifted and "a more favorable 
international climate is created." 

</TEXT>

