<H3> <TI>   Tomic Elected Speaker of Serbian Assembly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102192494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1842 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 1 Feb (TANJUG) -- Dragan Tomic, candidate 
for the Socialist Party of Serbia, was elected the new Serbian 
Assembly speaker by a majority of votes this evening. Out of 
247 deputies who attended the session, 125 voted for him, while 
Serbian Radical Party candidate Jorgovanka Tabakovic won 113 
votes. Two ballot papers were invalid, while five deputies of 
the Democratic Community of Vojvodina Hungarians abstained. 

</TEXT>

