<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik Denies Presence of FRY Soldiers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102165794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1551 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jagodina, Feb 1 (TANJUG) -- Assembly President of 
the Serbian Republic (RS) Momcilo Krajisnik on Tuesday said 
there was not a single soldier from the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia [FRY] on the territory of the state of the Bosnian 
Serbs and the RS was not receiving any arms from the F.R.Y. 
  Krajisnik said on Radio Jagodina (central Serbia) that the 
RS 
leadership "most categorically denies the reports circulating in 
U.S. circles that Army of Yugoslavia (VJ) units are crossing 
into the RS armed or unarmed to fight on the Serb side in the 
war in Bosnia-Herzegovina." 
  Co-chairman of the international conference on the former 
Yugoslavia Thorvald Stoltenberg said in New York on Monday there 
was no evidence that there were Army of Yugoslavia troops in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Krajisnik said it was true that the Muslim side had declared 
a longlasting war on the Bosnian Serbs and Bosnian Croats. He 
said the Bosnian Serbs were preparing to defend their territory, 
and the RS supreme command had proclaimed a (general) 
mobilization on Monday to that end. 
  "Our mobilization should be understood as a preventive 
response to the Muslim side's commitment to a longlasting war," 
Krajisnik said. He set out that the purpose of the mobilization 
was, among other things, to distribute the burden of the war 
among all RS citizens. 
  Krajisnik said he would meet again soon at Sarajevo airport 
with Bosnian Muslim Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic. 
  "The purpose of our meeting will be to replace the war 
option 
with a negotiating one, and I hope the meeting will be 
successful so that we could have concrete results in Geneva on 
February 10 (in the resumption of the peace talks)," Krajisnik 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-30348 </DOCNO>
