<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments Before Leaving </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202101094 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0900 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Before leaving Warsaw for Brussels, Waldemar 
Pawlak was asked whether Partnership for Peace would guarantee 
our NATO membership. He said: 
  [Begin Pawlak recording] I think this is not just the issue 
of Partnership for Peace but also a matter of the association 
with the European Union. Apart from the issue of security, 
political, military, and economic matters, partnership for 
development is also very important, and so is looking for forms 
of cooperation that would give Poland an opportunity for 
cooperation with the European Union as a partner. I think this 
is a fundamental condition, particularly because security issues 
may be a problem in the future, while economic problems are a 
problem today and should be solved today. [end recording] 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

