Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A NATO Headquarters fact-finding mission arrived in 
Poland today for discussions on the Partnership for Peace 
program. The delegation members are the permanent 
representatives of Denmark and Germany to NATO, and 
representatives of the supreme commander, Europe. The 
delegation will be received by Foreign Minister Andrzej 
Olechowski and Jerzy Milewski, secretary of state in the 
Ministry of National Defense. 

