<H3> <TI>   Speaker Receives Belarusian Ambassador to Warsaw </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102183694 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1550 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 1 Feb--Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy received 
Belarusian Ambassador Vladimir Senko on 1 February. The Sejm 
Chancellery has reported that the ambassador described the 
internal situation in Belarus in connection with the recent 
dismissal of Stanislav Shushkievich, chairman of the Belarusian 
parliament. 
  They discussed Belarusian-Russian relations in the areas of 
the unification of the monetary systems of both countries and 
closer economic cooperation. Much attention was devoted to the 
Partnership for Peace program, particularly the procedure of 
joining the program. 
  Both men expressed deep satisfaction with the state of 
bilateral relations but pointed out that the level of 
parliamentary contacts was insufficient. 
  At the end of the meeting, Ambassador Senko issued an 
official invitation to the Sejm speaker to visit Belarus, the 
Sejm Chancellery statement says. 

</TEXT>

