<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Silesian Railways To Stage 2-Hour Strike </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102204394 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1900 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A two-hour warning strike, which is to take place on 
2 February, has been announced for the entire Silesian DOKP 
[Regional State Railways Directorate] region by the Regional 
Solidarity Section of Railway Employees. The strike will start 
at 0700 [0600 GMT]. The traffic of passenger and freight trains 
will be halted. The other trade union confederations of the 
region are also to join in the strike. 
  The trade union members are demanding payment of the arrears 
of 850,000 zlotys [Z] due to them for last year and a pay raise 
of Z800,000 for each employee from 1 January. The trade unions 
have announced that, unless the Polish State Railways [PKP] 
General Directorate embarks on negotiations, the trade unions 
will make preparations for an all-out strike. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

