<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Receives Serbian Party Representatives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102173494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman received in the 
presidential palace today a delegation of the Serb National 
Party [in Croatia] comprising party chairman Milan Djukic, 
Veselin Pejnovic, and Veljko Miljevic, a statement from the 
president's office says. They informed President Tudjman about 
efforts made by their party toward normalizing Croatian-Serbian 
relations, particularly about the party's initiative called 
Peace Without Alternative. President Tudjman said that Croatia 
was resolved to make necessary efforts for the Croatian areas 
under UN protection to be reintegrated into the constitutional 
and legal order of the Republic of Croatia, to achieve the 
normalization of Croatian-Serbian relations, and to restore 
permanent peace and stability in the area, primarily through 
political means. The talks were also attended by the 
president's advisers Smiljko Sokol and Ivic Pasalic, the 
statement says. 

</TEXT>

