<DOCNO> FBIS3-30367 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu022_d_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-022 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Denies Talks With Israel on MiG-29 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102202094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an interview with TA SR [Slovak news agency], 
Defense Minister Imrich Andrejcak said that there have never 
been direct talks on MiG-29 aircraft between the Slovak Army and 
Israel. He was responding to the REUTER report in which Foreign 
Minister Jozef Moravcik said that Israel is able to refit this 
type of aircraft to Western standards and has allegedly already 
discussed cooperation. 
  Imrich Andrejcak said that the talks between Jozef Moravcik 
and the Israeli partners were not binding and were probably 
misinterpreted. However, the defense minister did not rule out 
the possibility that our Army would consider modernizing 
MiG-21's and MiG-29's as early as this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

