<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech Radio Most Popular Station in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102132994 Prague LIDOVE NOVINY in Czech 31 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0102132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague LIDOVE NOVINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Two-Thirds of Radio Audience Listen </F>
to Czech Radio"] 
  [Text] Prague--Last year, the number of listeners of Czech 
Radio (CRo) did not significantly decline. According to the 
surveys, the share of the CRo in the total number of radio 
listeners is approximately 65 percent. "The situation at the 
Praha, Radiozurnal, and Vltava radio stations is stable," 
Jaroslav Pochmon, director of programing, said when assessing 
1993. The most popular programs are the Radiozurnal Segments of 
Narrative and Music [bloky slova a hudby]. The Morning Stream 
[ranni proud] is listened to by an audience of 1.7 million, and 
the Praha station Good Morning [dobre jitro] has 1.2 million 
listeners. 
  On Saturday [29 January], the management of the Radio 
Metropolis radio station sent a proposal for a "nonstandard" 
solution to the complex situation of the CRo in connection with 
financing its newscast program on the long-waves band to CRo 
Director General Vlastimil Jezek. The Radio Metropolis proposes 
that a "nonbiased private entity with sufficient financial, 
professional, and political guarantees, assume the long-wave 
broadcast. A condition would be a close programing cooperation 
with Czech Radio. 

</TEXT>

