<F P=102>  LD0202091694 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0800 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0202091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 2 Feb--On Wednesday morning, Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak left for a two-day working visit to Brussels. 
  The head of the government will meet NATO acting Secretary 
General Sergio Silvio Balanzino; Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc 
Dehaene; Jacques Delors, chairman of the European Communities 
Commission; and Willem van Eekelen, secretary general of the 
Western European Union. 
  During his visit to NATO main headquarters, the prime 
minister will sign documents on Poland's membership in the 
Partnership for Peace program, which he was authorized to do by 
the government on 1 February. 
  The prime minister will also take part in a conference 
organized by the Center for Strategic and International Studies. 

